Sentencas: Graded and homogeneous CGO-LSCF composite electrodes deposited by Electrostatic Spray Deposition on an YSZ substrate have been studied with and without screen printed LSCF current collector.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of graded and homogeneous Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ composite electrodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy measurements have been performed in air at open circuit potential between 450 degrees C and 700 degrees C; and during isothermal treatments at 600 degrees C for 200 h; and at 800 degrees C for 12 h to estimate the relevance of such oxygen electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of graded and homogeneous Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ composite electrodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A thin and dense CGO layer is firstly deposited to avoid any chemical reaction between LSCF and YSZ.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of graded and homogeneous Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ composite electrodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: No significant increase of the polarization resistance has been evidenced during isothermal test at 600 degrees C for 200 h, proving good stability of the electrode.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of graded and homogeneous Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ composite electrodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using a LSCF current collector layer (CCL), the polarization resistance decreases by a 1.5 order of magnitude compared to samples with single cathode functional layer (CFL).
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of graded and homogeneous Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ composite electrodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical results do not conclusively indicate which composition presents lower polarization effects.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of graded and homogeneous Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ composite electrodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
